The knowledge is like money, or worldly food, it is consumable.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Just like money, the rich is relative. The knowledge is also relative. When every one know it, it become valueless.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The knowledge is like news, once we know it, it is not knowledge any more.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Only the Holy Spirit is the source of knowledge. Jesus said: those who believe me, in his body, the living water will spring.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>